body.note:
You can also use the internationalization technique described in the  section, but you will
      first need to hide the structure generated by the XSL HTML5 transformation (for example, the
        caption elements for tables and span
      elements for notes), then replace the labels with your own, defined in the CSS.
For example,
        to change the label and numbering for
        tables:.table--title-label{
  display:none;
}

*[class ~= "topic/table"] > caption:before{
  content: "Table " counter(tablecount) ". ";
}
In
        a similar way, you can alter the labels for
        notes:*[class ~= "topic/note"] > span.note__title {
  display:none;
}

*[class ~= "topic/note"]:before {
  content:" Note: ";
}
*[class ~= "topic/note"][type="caution"]:before {
  content: "Caution: ";
}
*[class ~= "topic/note"][type="important"]:before {
  content: "Important: ";
}
...
To
        identify the selectors for the elements that you need to hide, see .
